revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-20 19:34:29.000000000', 'files': ['lib/swift'], 'message': 'Explicitly set bind_ip in Swift server config files

Currently, the Swift proxy, object, account, and container servers bind
to IPv4 address 0.0.0.0 by default. In the case of a user setting
SERVICE_IP_VERSION=6 in their local.conf file, these Swift servers still
listen on 0.0.0.0 instead of ::, which causes a ./stack.sh run to fail.

This change explicitly sets the bind_ip variable in the Swift server
config files so that the servers bind to either 0.0.0.0 (when
SERVICE_IP_VERSION != 6) or :: (when SERVICE_IP_VERSION == 6).

This patch is related to the following patch for devstack IPv6 support:
    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/192329

Change-Id: Ie268c6daf5374e67ef8710a731c3af50ffdb821e
'}]
commit_message:
Explicitly set bind_ip in Swift server config files

Currently, the Swift proxy, object, account, and container servers bind
to IPv4 address 0.0.0.0 by default. In the case of a user setting
SERVICE_IP_VERSION=6 in their local.conf file, these Swift servers still
listen on 0.0.0.0 instead of ::, which causes a ./stack.sh run to fail.

This change explicitly sets the bind_ip variable in the Swift server
config files so that the servers bind to either 0.0.0.0 (when
SERVICE_IP_VERSION != 6) or :: (when SERVICE_IP_VERSION == 6).

This patch is related to the following patch for devstack IPv6 support:
    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/192329

Change-Id: Ie268c6daf5374e67ef8710a731c3af50ffdb821e

commit_message:
Move static files configuration to reduce settings.py churn

Operators don't like it when we change settings.py a lot, so this change
moves application configuration code (which can change a bunch) out of
settings.py into a separate file.

Change-Id: If099aa0d5d24827b1ce301f7c586647e6617826d
Closes-Bug: 1475447

commit_message:
Fix test_signal_returns_metadata wrong assertions

The test name implies we test that a signal returns metadata,
but actually we assert the opposite, which is that an async signal
returns None. So make the assertions to align with the test name.

Change-Id: Ib7b0bd602852684fa1213b04f95ceade2beb0bb6

commit_message:
Deprecate Spark 1.0.0

As discussed in the Sahara weekly meeting, this change request
removes 0.9.1 from the list of supported Spark versions and adds
the deprecation message to the validation phase for clusters
created for Spark 1.0.0, the same way as is done in the vanilla
plugin for version 2.4.1

Change-Id: I13965c09c083823511e66c7ae42317ceae1059cb
Implements: blueprint deprecate-spark-100

commit_message:
Allow ramdisk_id, kernel_id to be null on schema

Since is possible to create images with no
ramdisk_id, kernel_id parameters on glance v1,
then the schema-image.json needs to be modified to
allow null, string values for both attributes
and prevent LP #1447193 to happen with a glance v2
client.

APIImpact

Closes-Bug: #1447215
Related-Bug: #1447193

Change-Id: I645c797553ccaa84062f9ad28f2349ae738a0c96
Signed-off-by: Jorge Niedbalski <jorge.niedbalski@canonical.com>

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-07-21 17:59:12.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/l3/ha_router.py'], 'message': 'Fix race condition by using lock on enable_radvd

For an HA Router, radvd is spawned only in the Master Node.
KeepalivedStateChangeHandler after receiving the state notification
on the unix domain socket, would either enable/disable the radvd
process depending on the state of the HA Router. In parallel, if
there is a request to add an interface to the router, router.process()
would try to enable radvd in parallel. So there is a possible race
condition as two threads try to enable radvd in parallel. This patch
uses appropriate locking mechanism to prevent this race condition.

Closes-Bug: #1466663
Change-Id: I40df78cc57fcde5512336d9dfef88b3b06a69bcb
'}]
commit_message:
Fix race condition by using lock on enable_radvd

For an HA Router, radvd is spawned only in the Master Node.
KeepalivedStateChangeHandler after receiving the state notification
on the unix domain socket, would either enable/disable the radvd
process depending on the state of the HA Router. In parallel, if
there is a request to add an interface to the router, router.process()
would try to enable radvd in parallel. So there is a possible race
condition as two threads try to enable radvd in parallel. This patch
uses appropriate locking mechanism to prevent this race condition.

Closes-Bug: #1466663
Change-Id: I40df78cc57fcde5512336d9dfef88b3b06a69bcb

commit_message:
Add network templates functionality

Examples:

* To upload network template from filesystem path for specified environment:

    fuel --env 1 network-template --upload --dir path/to/directory

* To download network template to current directory for specified environment:

    fuel --env 1 network-template --download

Change-Id: Ic9af092596dca2b6c265b6280cfa85197d561a10
Implements: blueprint templates-for-networking

commit_message:
Prep $PROJECT and upper constraints for install

Before we can start enforcing constraints during tox runs we need to
ensure that the upper constraints from the requirements repo is in place
and up to date with the correct ref which may be latest $BRANCH or
$ZUUL_REF. Use zuul-cloner to ensure the state of both the project under
test and the constraints from the requirements repo.

To make use of this projects can update their tox targets to look for an
upper constraints file in the root dir of the project and have pip honor
those constraints when present.

Change-Id: I2829ba1bb0ce22b0f18080a1dc4ca7b1c77ce0e3

commit_message:
Tool to tie disconnected stacks together

This tool will deploy and update a set of disconnected stacks that need
to share limited information through parameters and outputs.

Much of this code is copy/pasted from python-heatclient's shell code as
there wasn't time to refactor python-heatclient to allow us to consume
the code directly.

An example of how a chunked master template is included as
chunk-heat-overcloud.yaml.

Change-Id: I99b4be2579e8a4f1f5836191d7c3343650cdb5a2

commit_message:
Dashboard ReOrg - prevent app.moulde.js from auto-collect

app/app.module.js has been added to _conf.html manually and therefore
should not be auto-collected. Previously we avoid auto-collecting
app/app.module.js by adding its sibling files / folders respectively and
that is inconvenient. This new approach is much better than the old one.
Now when we adding new files / folder as app/app.module.js' sibling we
do not need to change settings.py anymore.

This can make other efforts in Dashboard reOrg easier.

Change-Id: I7c09c906aee43a8e20a026c6cef275f8de7ee07b

commit_message:
Raise innodb_buffer_pool_size to 2G

100MB is not a production default. We expect the defaults to be used
in production whenever possible. While memory will vary, we would not
expect anybody to run an OpenStack cluster in production on a database
server with less than 8GB of RAM available. 2G leaves room for all of
the other things that we expect to be happening on a controller of that
size as well.

Note that this should not be merged until after these two changes which
will explicitly set the value to 100MB for testing/dev and which will
defer to the element if it is left unset:

Ia3cbffa9e795d22e8eddcc44db7d1548e8d99c91
I1b41b604286245c2fb83249778db835253c02fc5

Change-Id: I3c80e67eacd0a639e34a4742df7834a38bda2f17

commit_message:
Create RabbitMQ users on controller

Currently we rely on the existence of the guest user, but in RabbitMQ
3.3 this user is more restricted. We will want to create users for each
server eventually, but we have no good mechanism for doing so just yet.

For now, we'll just make sure the user requested in parameters is created
on the controller.

Change-Id: I2463312189e43b5ccfc63ac48335c14d64d0ce00
Related-Bug: #1315474
Closes-Bug: #1316309

commit_message:
Add trusts and stack_domain_admin to heat element

Recent changes to Heat require that we provide a domain and an
administrator for Heat to put in-instance users into. Making this
optional as a block so that we can operate with versions of Heat which
don't support these config options.

Also adds support for deferred_auth_method=trusts, also in an
optional block. While not strictly related they're both strongly
recommended.

Change-Id: I6fd03ffc1b5533660d9408f3335d11262e5d672b
Partial-Bug: #1287453

commit_message:
Start with a green field for RPM packaging

RDO and SUSE folks have agreed to start with a fresh
repo for collaborating on upstream packaging. In order to
sort out the issues, we start with a low hanging fruit
and iron out the differences there and will extend this
up the stack as things are progressing.

commit_message:
Add configuration show command

Create a `configuration show` command that displays the current
configuration of the CLI.  Different configurations can be
displayed using options such as --os-cloud.  Passwords and
tokens are redacted by default unless the --unmask
option is specified.

Closes-Bug: #1476729

Change-Id: I0792365d0c5fa526cd09c0ed88c6bb1e2cb813a7

commit_message:
Add missing "raise" when throwing exception.

Also, slightly relaxed the related check to allow 'remaining_uses' to be set
to None for redelegatable trusts. Previously, it would require that key
'remaining_uses' not even exist. The new check is still consistent with the
spec at http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/keystone-specs/api/v3/
identity-api-v3-os-trust-ext.html. All existing tests for redelegatable trusts
set 'remaining_uses' to None. Perhaps, other clients also do this. Not
relaxing the check would break them.

Finally, modified a unit test to expect the new exception
(400 instead of 403).

Change-Id: I989e138a98e43c398a7dd47f8f630737300fbf49
Closes-Bug: #1472054

commit_message:
No-python3 classifier for python-memcached

python-memcached doesn't support py34. keystonemiddleware py34 unit
tests fail with an error using python-memcached:

...
  File "/opt/stack/keystonemiddleware/.tox/py34/lib/python3.4/site-packages/memcache.py", line 1299, in send_cmd
    self.socket.sendall(cmd + '\r\n')
TypeError: 'str' does not support the buffer interface

This issue is reported to python-memcached:
https://github.com/linsomniac/python-memcached/issues/70

There's a pull request:
https://github.com/linsomniac/python-memcached/pull/67

Looks like python-memcached is an abandoned project.

Change-Id: Ie3dacedc9a355be914fe30f16dc40c58f779c46b

commit_message:
Suppressing the request when creating endpoint with invalid urls

When creating endpoint with invalid url, such as uuid string
or "http://127.0.0.1:8774 /v1.1/\$(tenant_i d)s", it is now
suppressed.

This bug is simply about the substitutions,so we should only check
the substitutions and the whitespace.

The bug occurs when use the keystone command: keystone endpoint-create.
The Keystone command line interface packaged in python-keystoneclient
only supports the Identity v2.0 API.
So only v2.0 API is modified in this commit.

Partial-Bug: #1471034
Change-Id: I6c95cce022c87cae1c39e7ff3345edb91c68d7d3

The sample config updater had a couple of problems

1) It would steal a different proposal bot review (e.g., if there
was a review for requirements update it would be replaced with a
config update. The fix for this is to fetch reviews for the
topic.

2) The topic was incorrect since it was like

Change-Id: I6fa5c78d7ea18aecbb96c573be78a42560b3b158
'}]
commit_message:
Sample config updater fixes

The sample config updater had a couple of problems

1) It would steal a different proposal bot review (e.g., if there
was a review for requirements update it would be replaced with a
config update. The fix for this is to fetch reviews for the
topic.

2) The topic was incorrect since it was like
openstack/openstack/keystone/genconf, there's an extra "openstack/".

Change-Id: I6fa5c78d7ea18aecbb96c573be78a42560b3b158

commit_message:
Nested Quota : cloud_admin and project_admin creation

Two roles ,namely project_admin and cloud_admin are created
to control the quota operations.

With heirarchical projects in place, it is quite necessary to have
flexible as well as conrolled access to various projects.

For updating or deleting the quota of a sub-project, the user
should  have the role of either cloud_admin or admin, or
project_admin in the parent project.

But only admin or cloud_admin can update or delete the quota of
a root project.

Change-Id: I05810ecb137862550be12c4b82099ee1363a4254
Implements:  bp nested-quota-driver-api

In the case of nested projects, when the quota of a child

commit_message:
Removal of redundant context checking in wsgi.py file

In the case of nested projects, when the quota of a child
project is increased, there will be a corresponding reduction
in the free quota of the parent.So, while the quota of a
project is getting updated, it makes sense to scope the token
to the parent instead to the project itself.

But if the token is scoped to the parent , then wsgi.py will
block it because the project_id in token and url are different.
So there is no need of checking the context at multiple places.
Let the individual apis take decision on the context.Currenly
all the apis are checking the context individually. So a global
or common context checking is redundant.

Change-Id: I8e7338502f9fd5e0d92cd4f5c2e8166e3a3679d8
Implements:  bp nested-quota-driver-api

Currently, magnum will create a container object first and save it in magnum

commit_message:
Do not inspect contianer doesn't exist.

Currently, magnum will create a container object first and save it in magnum
DB, but in some cases it will fail to start in docker cluster. Later when
call container_show, _find_container_by_name will return {}, with {} to
inspect docker instance, docker client will raise an exception:

NullResource: image or container param is undefined.

it will cause magnum api raise an internal Error:
ERROR: Docker internal Error: image or container param is undefined (HTTP 500)

This patch checks _find_container_by_name return value before passing
inspect_container() to avoid exception happen.

Closes-Bug: #1475164
Change-Id: I7d07f657908b26fbd7ba245a9138a5dc613b4938

commit_message:
Removing Network Profile support in stable/kilo

Network profile is not supported in stable/kilo by the Cisco N1KV
ML2 driver. As the patch for enabling/disabling network profile
support based on a configurable parameter was rejected, this patch
pulls out the network profile code completly from stable/kilo.

This patch is necessary for horizon to be functional with Cisco
N1KV ML2 driver.

Change-Id: I1ef2f489c9bb2adfbe3174c3667539c59562966f
Closes-bug: #1475190

commit_message:
Fix getting wwpn information in infortrend driver for DS4000

For DS4000, we need to use 'BID' to get the wwpn information
because target ID was not 112 or 113 on DS4000.

It is compatible with other infortrend product.

Closes-Bug: 1469983

Change-Id: I230f79c1efe78bc49edb81ab605a2c70ffbdd31c

commit_message:
Fix properties extracting from image with glance api v2

When a volume is created using the glance v1 API, the non based
properties places in 'properties' dict, and nova is expected
to find them here. Otherwise api's v2 return custom image properties
as base properties, so nova can't find them in volume 'image
properties'.

This change add new glance call to get image schema, it allows
extract custom properties from image.

Closes-Bug: 1323660

Change-Id: Ib54bb6759b27334294fb2c6d2c0bfe4eae3d0920

commit_message:
Allow passing table argument to construct IpRouteCommand

The various methods of IpRouteCommand also work with a non-default
table.  Instead of passing an explicit table argument to each command,
this change allows constructing an instance of IpRouteCommand which
always works on the given table much like we pass the namespace on
creation instead of passing it to each command individually.

Change-Id: I503aa986208347ccc1cb5f37bdb36f77553eee70
Partially-Implements: blueprint address-scopes

subject: Ensure we check callback '_is_periodic' on add
revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-07-09 21:25:09.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/api.rst', 'futurist/periodics.py', 'futurist/tests/test_periodics.py'], 'message': "Ensure we check callback '_is_periodic' on add

Instead of always adding we should make sure we check
the callback attribute '_is_periodic' and avoid adding
if this is set to false.

This always has the `add` function return whether the
add was successful or not (using the '_is_periodic' attribute
to affect this return result).

Whats returned from `add` (and is also accessible now via
`iter_watchers`) is a new watcher object which provides a
read-only view on the callback (and its metrics) as it gets ran
by the worker.

Change-Id: Ie77248f04125c9f61a336d45f25ac1eaa53ab497
"}]
commit_message:
Ensure we check callback '_is_periodic' on add

Instead of always adding we should make sure we check
the callback attribute '_is_periodic' and avoid adding
if this is set to false.

This always has the `add` function return whether the
add was successful or not (using the '_is_periodic' attribute
to affect this return result).

Whats returned from `add` (and is also accessible now via
`iter_watchers`) is a new watcher object which provides a
read-only view on the callback (and its metrics) as it gets ran
by the worker.

Change-Id: Ie77248f04125c9f61a336d45f25ac1eaa53ab497

commit_message:
Fix filtering apps by category is broken

Div with id 'apps_carousel' will be hidden if a category with no apps belong to.
As a result, filtering apps by category would be broken then even if selete apps
with filter 'ALL'.

Change-Id: I3467c63555ffd50d25c1d1428ce3c481a0de31fc
Closes-Bug: #1454865

commit_message:
Contextlib.nested is deprecated

Contextlib.nested is deprecated since version 2.7. The with-statement
now supports this functionality directly (without the confusing
error prone quirks).

Change-Id: I6c6d1dbd2cbf35ecf0ac9c70879c148d70f81b06
Closes-Bug: #1477428

commit_message:
Add new ovs DB API to inquire interfaces name list in a bridge

In OVS, ports don't equal to interfaces when a bond port created. This patch
add the new API get_iface_name_list to get the interfaces' name, and it's
supplementary to the current get_port_name_list API.

Change-Id: I29c220e099b8dcf78248e2d660c435578bb2932d
Partial-Bug: #1460494

commit_message:
Removes replace-on-update for SwiftSignalHandle resource

Rebuilding the resource on every stack update results in a new
url being generated. This causes any depending resources to
be rebuilt, even when there are no changes in the template.

Change-Id: I9113f4f6bdd53379e459e48c5a7a41ce958727ae
Closes-Bug: #1473692

revisions:
[{'number': 9, 'created': '2015-07-16 22:58:44.000000000', 'files': ['nova/objects/pci_device.py', 'nova/tests/unit/objects/test_objects.py', 'nova/objects/instance.py'], 'message': "Fix the incorrect PciDeviceList version number

The following commit missed to bump the related list when bumping the
object version.

    commit 1d4ad44f15503b8710ff59dea9f5e3f4894d56fb
    Author: Przemyslaw Czesnowicz <przemyslaw.czesnowicz@intel.com>
    Date:   Thu Nov 20 12:04:05 2014 +0000

        Add numa_node to PCIDevice

        The change extends the PCI device model and its DB representation.
        Query libvirt for the PCI devices numa node.

This patch adds the necessary changes to master. We only bump the
PciDeviceList version, and add a backporting rule to obj_relationship
dictionary of the Instance object, to start sending the new version with
1.20 version of the instance (we are currently on 1.21).

Landing this patch fixes versioning going forward, and all interactions
that request the PciDeviceList through the Instance object, however
applying the stable/kilo backport of this is required for Kilo nodes to
start requesting the latest version of PciDevice through PciDeviceList.

We can't send 1.2 PciDeviceList to Kilo nodes yet because of
related-bug 1475254 , so we have to backport this to Kilo first before
we can start sending the 1.2 to Kilo nodes.

Related-bug: #1474074
Change-Id: Id743848061d2bcd64d785979c7a11ee7c945f06b
"}]
commit_message:
Fix the incorrect PciDeviceList version number

The following commit missed to bump the related list when bumping the
object version.

    commit 1d4ad44f15503b8710ff59dea9f5e3f4894d56fb
    Author: Przemyslaw Czesnowicz <przemyslaw.czesnowicz@intel.com>
    Date:   Thu Nov 20 12:04:05 2014 +0000

        Add numa_node to PCIDevice

        The change extends the PCI device model and its DB representation.
        Query libvirt for the PCI devices numa node.

This patch adds the necessary changes to master. We only bump the
PciDeviceList version, and add a backporting rule to obj_relationship
dictionary of the Instance object, to start sending the new version with
1.20 version of the instance (we are currently on 1.21).

Landing this patch fixes versioning going forward, and all interactions
that request the PciDeviceList through the Instance object, however
applying the stable/kilo backport of this is required for Kilo nodes to
start requesting the latest version of PciDevice through PciDeviceList.

We can't send 1.2 PciDeviceList to Kilo nodes yet because of
related-bug 1475254 , so we have to backport this to Kilo first before
we can start sending the 1.2 to Kilo nodes.

Related-bug: #1474074
Change-Id: Id743848061d2bcd64d785979c7a11ee7c945f06b

commit_message:
Add remote procedure call tunables to nova and neutron

This allows us to override the default settings, which is useful for
large deployments or deploying a large number of instances.  It also
uses an unused variable in neutron for setting the rpc_backend.

Change-Id: I83d11eb79b30dda51c6f738433ca960a0f63246e
Closes-bug: 1471926

commit_message:
Non Disruptive Backup

Currently a backup operation can only be performed when the volume is
detached. This blueprint proposes the following changes in order to do
a non-disruptive backup while the volume is still attached:

For the LVM driver, a temporary snapshot will be created and backup
will be performed by reading from the local path of the snapshot.
After that, the temporary snapshot will be deleted.

For other drivers, a default implementation will be provided to
create a temporary volume from the source volume and backup will be
performed by attaching the temporary volume and reading from it.
After it is done, the temporary volume will be detached and deleted.

For other drivers, a more optimized approach will also be provided to
create a temporary snapshot, attach the snapshot, backup the snapshot,
and then detach and delete the temporary snapshot. This optimized
approach is not required. If a driver has not implemented attach
snapshot, the default implementation with a temporary volume will
be used.

DocImpact
blueprint non-disruptive-backup

Change-Id: I069d86d315dd2c83d43d694087f2dcc2f0b0752b

commit_message:
New network interface and amphora interface

Network interface has been changed to be a straight wrapper around the core
neutron API (networks, subnets, ports).  The amphora driver absorbs the old
network driver methods like plug_vip, allocate_vip, etc.  These have been
created as separate interface for now so that the old code still works and once
the new implementations have been added they can be changed to become the real
interfaces and the old interfaces and implementations can be removed.

Change-Id: I50b86169bb78af7f09a77bd5185215c5cefe8564

commit_message:
Fix for return traffic from VIP blackholing

Fixes bug that caused amphorae to send reply traffic to the wrong interface.
This fix sends any traffic that comes in on the VIP interface, back through
the same VIP interface.  All of this is being done without making calls to
the network driver and using what is passed in from the controller worker.
This actually makes the code more complex than if we were able to call neutron
to grab ports and subnets.  The current code will not scale when there is a lot
of ports and/or subnets under a network because right now it has to be all
loaded up front in memory.  I have ideas on solving this, but all will require
a bit of up front work.

Also cleaned up the ssh driver when adding ips and raising interfaces.  The
interfaces, however, will not persist through reboots now, but I do not octavia
will be rebooting amphorae very often.  If we every need that functionality
again it should be re-added in a cleaner way.

Change-Id: If143c02007264ea0c89e2fd30991984da7c019b2
Closes-Bug: #1453951

commit_message:
Add more network models to enhance decoupling

Added subnet, port, and fixed ip network data models to facilitate more loose
coupling because this information is needed in other drivers and it does not
make sense for those drivers to have to make direct calls to services that a
networking driver would do and abstract away from them.

This also required changing the flows, tasks, and driver methods to retrieve
and accept more data.  I've also chosen to just go with the same data model
as neutron as that will be our primary networking service, so if some other
networking service in the future wants a network driver implemented then that
driver will have to translate whatever data model is uses into the one that
fits neutron.

Change-Id: I54a8c52a70e20c47a6201cf10cf12fc0b720646f

commit_message:
OpenStack community activity report Q2, 2015

This report is produced quarterly to give Community Managers and
OpenStack Foundation's management better insights on development
activities and online conversations. The quantitative and qualitative
assessment start from tracking actions across all OpenStack git
repositories, gerrit code reviews, bug trackers as well as IRC channels,
mailing lists and questions/answers.

Change-Id: I31fb5b67de2acc60def378399eb2dde3e43810ae

commit_message:
Add a proxy inifile provider

Create a proxy inifile provider that will sit between the openstack
configuration providers (ie. keystone_config) and the actual ini_setting
provider.

Adding such a component will give us more flexibility on the ini_setting
provider. With that in place we could :

 * Test new feature with the provider - merge them upstream when validated
 * Bypass upstream limit if our queries are not valid for upstream.

By inheriting the provider we don't fork and hence should remain
compatible with the next releases of puppetlabs-inifile

Change-Id: I061371d8cf2faf928019161e635e1b4252a6b433

commit_message:
Operations to deactivate and reactivate an image

In order to provide administrators a way to temporarily prevent
the download and usage of a potentially harmful image, this
spec proposes the addition of operations to Glance supporting
the concept of a 'deactivated' image.

Addresses: bp deactivate-image

DocImpact APIImpact

Change-Id: I2ec467e33d5d376ede6e3f63245e0e0a82f04bdb

commit_message:
Change a value of a request body in "POST /v3/groups"

In a sample of q request body of "POST v3/groups",
the following values should be changed:

 "description" should be "Developers cleared for work on secret projects".
 "domain_id" should be "161718".
 "name" should be "Secure Developers".

Because a sample of a response body is as follows:
{
    "group": {
        "description": "Developers cleared for work on secret projects",
        "domain_id": "161718",
        "id": "101112",
        "links": {
            "self": "http://identity:35357/v3/groups/101112"
        },
        "name": "Secure Developers"
    }
}

For details, please see http://developer.openstack.org/api-ref-identity-v3.html#createGroup

Change-Id: I78cd3d91ef7c3161914268fdda43203a963224a4
Closes-Bug: #1477557

following values should be changed:

"description": "James Doe's user",
"name": "James Doe",

Because a sample of a request body is as follows:
{
    "user": {
        "default_project_id": "263fd9",
        "description": "Jim Doe's user",
        "domain_id": "1789d1",
        "email": "jdoe@example.com",
        "enabled": true,
        "name": "James Doe",

}

commit_message:
Install dependencies needed for gems in macro

Some of the puppet jobs installed dependencies needed to compile
commonly used gems.  The infra puppet jobs lacked that.  Move that
logic into the 'uninstall-puppet' macro and rename it to 'puppet-
prepare-node' to reflect that it's a general macro for preparing
a node to run puppet jobs.

Apply the macro everywhere 'uninstall-puppet' was used before.
This adds the packaging logic to the infra jobs and some OpenStack
puppet jobs.

Change-Id: Ib504f3fea4713f14bf3dc2e9659fad0e999f8146
